name: Bulbasaur
description: The seed on its back is filled with nutrients. The seed grows steadily larger as its body grows.

name: Ivysaur
description: Exposure to sunlight adds to its strength. Sunlight also makes the bud on its back grow larger.

name: Venusaur
description: By spreading the broad petals of its flower and catching the sun's rays$ it fills its body with power.

name: Charmander
description: The flame on its tail shows the strength of its life force. If it is weak$ the flame also burns weakly.

name: Charmeleon
description: It is very hotheaded by nature$ so it constantly seeks opponents. It calms down only when it wins.

name: Charizard
description: If CHARIZARD becomes furious$ the flame at the tip of its tail flares up in a light blue shade.

name: Squirtle
description: The shell is soft when it is born. It soon becomes so resilient$ prodding fingers will bounce off it.

name: Wartortle
description: It is a well-established symbol of longevity. If its shell has algae on it$ that WARTORTLE is very old.

name: Blastoise
description: It deliberately makes itself heavy so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.

name: Caterpie
description: For protection$ it releases a horrible stench from the antennae on its head to drive away enemies.

name: Metapod
description: Inside the shell$ it is soft and weak as it prepares to evolve. It stays motionless in the shell.

name: Butterfree
description: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.

name: Weedle
description: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

name: Kakuna
description: Although it is a cocoon$ it can move a little. It can extend its poison barb if it is attacked.

name: Beedrill
description: It can take down any opponent with its powerful poison stingers. It sometimes attacks in swarms.

name: Pidgey
description: It usually hides in tall grass. Because it dislikes fighting$ it protects itself by kicking up sand.

name: Pidgeotto
description: It has outstanding vision. However high it flies$ it is able to distinguish the movements of its prey.

name: Pidgeot
description: Its well-developed chest muscles make it strong enough to whip up a gusty windstorm with just a few flaps.

name: Rattata
description: It eats anything. Wherever food is available$ it will settle down and produce offspring continuously.

name: Raticate
description: Gnaws on anything with its tough fangs. It can even topple concrete buildings by gnawing on them.

name: Spearow
description: It flaps its short wings to flush out insects from tall grass. It then plucks them with its stubby beak.

name: Fearow
description: It shoots itself suddenly high into the sky$ then plummets down in one fell swoop to strike its prey.

name: Ekans
description: It can freely detach its jaw to swallow large prey whole. It can become too heavy to move$ however.

name: Arbok
description: Transfixing prey with the face-like pattern on its belly$ it binds and poisons the frightened victim.

name: Pikachu
description: This intelligent Pokemon roasts hard berries with electricity to make them tender enough to eat.

name: Raichu
description: When its electricity builds$ its muscles are stimulated$ and it becomes more aggressive than usual.

name: Sandshrew
description: If it fell from a great height$ this Pokemon could save itself by rolling into a ball and bouncing.

name: Sandslash
description: In an attempt to hide itself$ it will run around at top speed to kick up a blinding dust storm.

name: Nidoran ¬
description: The poison hidden in its small horn is extremely potent. Even a tiny scratch can have fatal results.

name: Nidorina
description: When feeding its young$ it first chews the food into a paste$ then spits it out for the offspring.

name: Nidoqueen
description: Its body is covered with needle-like scales. It never shows signs of shrinking from any attack.

name: Nidoran £
description: It is small$ but its horn is filled with poison. It charges then stabs with the horn to inject poison.

name: Nidorino
description: It raises its big ears to check its surroundings. If it senses anything$ it attacks immediately.

name: Nidoking
description: It swings its big tail around during battle. If its foe flinches$ it will charge with its sturdy body.

name: Clefairy
description: The moonlight that it stores in the wings on its back apparently gives it the ability to float in midair.

name: Clefable
description: With its acute hearing$ it can pick up sounds from far away. It usually hides in quiet places.

name: Vulpix
description: As it develops$ its single white tail gains color and splits into six. It is quite warm and cuddly.

name: Ninetales
description: Some legends claim that each of its nine tails has its own unique type of special mystical power.

name: Jigglypuff
description: If it inflates to sing a lullaby$ it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.

name: Wigglytuff
description: Their fur feels so good that if two of them snuggle together$ they won't want to be separated.

name: Zubat
description: While flying$ it constantly emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings.

name: Golbat
description: However hard its victim's hide may be$ it punctures with sharp fangs and gorges itself with blood.

name: Oddish
description: Awakened by moonlight$ it roams actively at night. In the day$ it stays quietly underground.

name: Gloom
description: What appears to be drool is actually sweet honey. It is very sticky and clings stubbornly if touched.

name: Vileplume
description: It has the world's largest petals. With every step$ the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

name: Paras
description: It is doused with mushroom spores when it is born. As its body grows$ mushrooms sprout from its back.

name: Parasect
description: It stays mostly in dark$ damp places$ the preference not of the bug$ but of the big mushroom on its back.

name: Venonat
description: Its eyes also function as radar units. It catches and eats small bugs that hide in darkness.

name: Venomoth
description: When it attacks$ it flaps its large wings violently to scatter its poisonous powder all around.

name: Diglett
description: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light$ its blood heats up$ causing it to grow weak.

name: Dugtrio
description: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby$ making it easier for it to burrow.

name: Meowth
description: It is fascinated by round objects. It can't stop playing with them until it tires and falls asleep.

name: Persian
description: Many adore it for its sophisticated air. However$ it will lash out and scratch for little reason.

name: Psyduck
description: It has mystical powers but doesn't recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.

name: Golduck
description: When it swims at full speed using its long$ webbed limbs$ its forehead somehow begins to glow.

name: Mankey
description: It is extremely ill-tempered. Groups of them will attack any handy target for no reason.

name: Primeape
description: If approached while asleep$ it may awaken and angrily give chase in a groggy state of semi-sleep.

name: Growlithe
description: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Arcanine
description: This legendary Chinese Pokemon is considered magnificent. Many people are enchanted by its grand mane.

name: Poliwag
description: Because it is inept at walking on its newly grown legs$ it always  swims around in water.

name: Poliwhirl
description: The swirl on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it may gradually cause drowsiness.

name: Poliwrath
description: This strong and skilled swimmer is even capable of crossing the Pacific Ocean just by kicking.

name: Abra
description: It senses impending attacks and teleports away to safety before the actual attacks can strike.

name: Kadabra
description: It possesses strong spiritual power. The more danger it faces$ the stronger its psychic power.

name: Alakazam
description: Closing both its eyes heightens all its other senses. This enables it to use its abilities to their extremes.

name: Machop
description: Always brimming with power$ it passes time by lifting boulders. Doing so makes it even stronger.

name: Machoke
description: It always goes at its full power$ but this very tough and durable Pokemon never gets tired.

name: Machamp
description: It quickly swings its four arms to rock its opponents with ceaseless punches and chops from all angles.

name: Bellsprout
description: Even though its body is extremely skinny$ it is blindingly fast when catching its prey.

name: Weepinbell
description: Even though it is filled with acid$ it does not melt because it also oozes a protective fluid.

name: Victreebel
description: Acid that has dissolved many prey becomes sweeter$ making it even more effective at attracting prey.

name: Tentacool
description: When the tide goes out$ dehydrated TENTACOOL remains can be found washed up on the shore.

name: Tentacruel
description: Its 80 tentacles absorb water and stretch almost endlessly to constrict its prey and enemies.

name: Geodude
description: Most people may not notice$ but a closer look should reveal that there are many GEODUDE around.

name: Graveler
description: With a free and uncaring nature$ it doesn't mind if pieces break off while it rolls down mountains.

name: Golem
description: It sheds its skin once a year. The discarded shell immediately hardens and crumbles away.

name: Ponyta
description: It is a weak runner immediately after birth. It gradually becomes faster by chasing after its parents.

name: Rapidash
description: At full gallop$ its four hooves barely touch the ground because it moves so incredibly fast.

name: Slowpoke
description: It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail$ it won't even notice for a whole day.

name: Slowbro
description: If the tail-biting SHELLDER is thrown off in a harsh battle$ it reverts to being an ordinary SLOWPOKE.

name: Magnemite
description: It is attracted by electromagnetic waves. It may approach Trainers if they are using their Pokegear.

name: Magneton
description: Three MAGNEMITE are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

name: Farfetch'd
description: If anyone tries to disturb where the essential plant stalks grow$ it uses its own stalk to thwart them.

name: Doduo
description: By alternately raising and lowering its two heads$ it balances itself to be more stable while running.

name: Dodrio
description: It collects data and plans three times as wisely$ but it may think too much and fall into a state of immobility.

name: Seel
description: Although it can't walk well on land$ it is a graceful swimmer. It especially loves being in frigid seas.

name: Dewgong
description: Its streamlined body has little drag in water. The colder the temperature$ the friskier it gets.

name: Grimer
description: As it moves$ it loses bits of its body$ from which new GRIMER emerge. This worsens the stench around it.

name: Muk
description: They love to gather in smelly areas where sludge accumulates$ making the stench around them worse.

name: Shellder
description: It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.

name: Cloyster
description: Once it slams its shell shut$ it is impossible to open$ even by those with superior strength.

name: Gastly
description: With its gas-like body$ it can sneak into any place it desires. However$ it can be blown away by wind.

name: Haunter
description: In total darkness$ where nothing is visible$ HAUNTER lurks$ silently stalking its next victim.

name: Gengar
description: It steals heat from its surroundings. If you feel a sudden chill$ it is certain that a GENGAR appeared.

name: Onix
description: It twists and squirms through the ground. The thunderous roar of its tunneling echoes a long way.

name: Drowzee
description: If you think that you had a good dream but you can't remember it$ a DROWZEE has probably eaten it.

name: Hypno
description: When it is very hungry$ it puts humans it meets to sleep$ then it feasts on their dreams.

name: Krabby
description: If it senses danger approaching$ it cloaks itself with bubbles from its mouth so it will look bigger.

name: Kingler
description: It can hardly lift its massive$ overgrown pincer. The pincer's size makes it difficult to aim properly.

name: Voltorb
description: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven$ a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Electrode
description: It is dangerous. If it has too much electricity and has nothing to do$ it amuses itself by exploding.

name: Exeggcute
description: Their shells are very durable. Even if they crack$ they can survive without spilling their contents.

name: Exeggutor
description: Its three heads think independently. However$ they are friendly and never appear to squabble.

name: Cubone
description: If it is sad or lonely$ the skull it wears shakes and emits a plaintive and mournful sound.

name: Marowak
description: It has been seen pounding boulders with the bone it carries in order to tap out messages to others.

name: Hitmonlee
description: This amazing Pokemon has an awesome sense of balance. It can kick in succession from any position.

name: Hitmonchan
description: Its punches slice the air. However$ it seems to need a short break after fighting for three minutes.

name: Lickitung
description: Its tongue has well-developed nerves that run to the very tip$ so it can be deftly manipulated.

name: Koffing
description: Its thin$ filmy body is filled with gases that cause constant sniffles$ coughs and teary eyes.

name: Weezing
description: If one of the twin KOFFING inflates$ the other one deflates. It constantly mixes its poisonous gases.

name: Rhyhorn
description: It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.

name: Rhydon
description: Its rugged hide protects it from even the heat of lava. However$ the hide also makes it insensitive.

name: Chansey
description: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However$ it is extremely fast at running away.

name: Tangela
description: The vines that cloak its entire body are always jiggling. They effectively unnerve its foes.

name: Kangaskhan
description: If it is safe$ the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.

name: Horsea
description: If attacked by a larger enemy$ it quickly swims to safety by adeptly controlling its well-developed dorsal fin.

name: Seadra
description: An examination of its cells revealed the presence of a gene not found in HORSEA. It became a hot topic.

name: Goldeen
description: Its dorsal$ pectoral and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the water dancer.

name: Seaking
description: During spawning season$ SEAKING gather from all over$ causing rivers to appear a brilliant red.

name: Staryu
description: At night$ the middle of its body slowly flickers with the same rhythm as a human heartbeat.

name: Starmie
description: The middle section of its body is called the core. It glows in a different color each time it is seen.

name: Mr. Mime
description: A skilled mime from birth$ it gains the ability to create invisible objects as it matures.

name: Scyther
description: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes$ moving too fast for the human eye to track.

name: Jynx
description: It rocks its body rhythmically. It appears to alter the rhythm depending on how it is feeling.

name: Electabuzz
description: Electricity runs across the surface of its body. In darkness$ its entire body glows a whitish-blue.

name: Magmar
description: It dislikes cold places$ so it blows scorching flames to make the environment suitable for itself.

name: Pinsir
description: With its pincer horns$ it digs burrows to sleep in at night. In the morning$ damp soil clings to its body.

name: Tauros
description: They fight each other by locking horns. The herd's protector takes pride in its battle-scarred horns.

name: Magikarp
description: An underpowered$ pathetic Pokemon. It may jump high on rare occasions$ but usually not more than seven feet.

name: Gyarados
description: They say that during past strife$ GYARADOS would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake.

name: Lapras
description: They have gentle hearts. Because they rarely fight$ many have been caught. Their number has dwindled.

name: Ditto
description: It can transform into anything. When it sleeps$ it changes into a stone to avoid being attacked.

name: Eevee
description: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

name: Vaporeon
description: When VAPOREON's fins begin to vibrate$ it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.

name: Jolteon
description: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

name: Flareon
description: It stores some of the air it inhales in its internal flame pouch$ which heats it to over 3$000 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
description: It is a manmade Pokemon. Since it doesn't breathe$ people are eager to try it in any environment.

name: Omanyte
description: Revived from an ancient fossil$ this Pokemon uses air stored in its shell to sink and rise in water.

name: Omastar
description: Apparently$ it cracked SHELLDER's shell with its sharp fangs and sucked out the insides.

name: Kabuto
description: On rare occasions$ some have been found as fossils which they became while hiding on the ocean floor.

name: Kabutops
description: In the water$ it tucks in its limbs to become more compact$ then it wiggles its shell to swim fast.

name: Aerodactyl
description: A vicious Pokemon from the distant past$ it appears to have flown by spreading its wings and gliding.

name: Snorlax
description: What sounds like its cry may actually be its snores or the rumblings of its hungry belly.

name: Articuno
description: The magnificent$ seemingly translucent wings of this legendary bird Pokemon are said to be made of ice.

name: Zapdos
description: This legendary bird Pokemon causes savage thunderstorms by flapping its glittering wings.

name: Moltres
description: This legendary Pokemon scatters embers with every flap of its wings. It is a thrilling sight to behold.

name: Dratini
description: It is born large to start with. It repeatedly sheds its skin as it steadily grows longer.

name: Dragonair
description: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body$ the weather will begin to change instantly.

name: Dragonite
description: It is said that this Pokemon constantly flies over the immense seas and rescues drowning people.

name: Mewtwo
description: Because its battle abilities were raised to the ultimate level$ it thinks only of defeating its foes.

name: Mew
description: Apparently$ it appears only to those people who are pure of heart and have a strong desire to see it.

name: Chikorita
description: A sweet aroma gently wafts from the leaf on its head. It is docile and loves to soak up sunrays.

name: Bayleef
description: The scent of spices comes from around its neck. Somehow$ sniffing it makes you want to fight.

name: Meganium
description: The aroma that rises from its petals contains a substance that calms aggressive feelings.

name: Cyndaquil
description: It is timid$ and always curls itself up in a ball. If attacked$ it flares up its back for protection.

name: Quilava
description: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.

name: Typhlosion
description: If its rage peaks$ it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

name: Totodile
description: Its powerful$ well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.

name: Croconaw
description: If it loses a fang$ a new one grows back in its place. There are always 48 fangs lining its mouth.

name: Feraligatr
description: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws$ it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

name: Sentret
description: A very cautious Pokemon$ it raises itself up using its tail to get a better view of its surroundings.

name: Furret
description: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokemon to enter.

name: Hoothoot
description: It always stands on one foot. It changes feet so fast$ the movement can rarely be seen.

name: Noctowl
description: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.

name: Ledyba
description: It is very timid. It will be afraid to move if it is alone. But it will be active if it is in a group.

name: Ledian
description: When the stars flicker in the night sky$ it flutters about$ scattering a glowing powder.

name: Spinarak
description: It lies still in the same pose for days in its web$ waiting for its unsuspecting prey to wander close.

name: Ariados
description: It spins string not only from its rear but also from its mouth. It's hard to tell which end is which.

name: Crobat
description: It flies so silently through the dark on its four wings that it may not be noticed even when nearby.

name: Chinchou
description: It shoots positive and negative electricity between the tips of its two antennae and zaps its enemies.

name: Lanturn
description: The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea's surface from a depth of over three miles.

name: Pichu
description: It is not yet skilled at storing electricity. It may send out a jolt if amused or startled.

name: Cleffa
description: Because of its unusual$ starlike silhouette$ people believe that it came here on a meteor.

name: Igglybuff
description: It has a very soft body. If it starts to roll$ it will bounce all over and be impossible to stop.

name: Togepi
description: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

name: Togetic
description: They say that it will appear before kindhearted$ caring people and shower them with happiness.

name: Natu
description: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown$ it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.

name: Xatu
description: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

name: Mareep
description: If static electricity builds in its body$ its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

name: Flaaffy
description: As a result of storing too much electricity$ it developed patches where even downy wool won't grow.

name: Ampharos
description: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

name: Bellossom
description: BELLOSSOM gather at times and seem to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

name: Marill
description: The tip of its tail$ which contains oil that is lighter than water$ lets it swim without drowning.

name: Azumarill
description: By keeping still and listening intently$ it can tell what is in even wild$ fast-moving rivers.

name: Sudowoodo
description: Although it always pretends to be a tree$ its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

name: Politoed
description: If POLIWAG and POLIWHIRL hear its echoing cry$ they respond by gathering from far and wide.

name: Hoppip
description: To keep from being blown away by the wind$ they gather in clusters. But they do enjoy gentle breezes.

name: Skiploom
description: The bloom on top of its head opens and closes as the temperature fluctuates up and down.

name: Jumpluff
description: Once it catches the wind$ it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores-- it can even float around the world.

name: Aipom
description: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

name: Sunkern
description: It may plummet from the sky. If attacked by a SPEAROW$ it will violently shake its leaves.

name: Sunflora
description: It converts sunlight into energy. In the darkness after sunset$ it closes its petals and becomes still.

name: Yanma
description: If it flaps its wings really fast$ it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

name: Wooper
description: This Pokemon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

name: Quagsire
description: This carefree Pokemon has an easy-going nature. While swimming$ it always bumps into boat hulls.

name: Espeon
description: It uses the fine hair that covers its body to sense air currents and predict its enemy's actions.

name: Umbreon
description: When agitated$ this Pokemon protects itself by spraying poisonous sweat from its pores.

name: Murkrow
description: Feared and loathed by many$ it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

name: Slowking
description: It has incredible intellect and intuition. Whatever the situation$ it remains calm and collected.

name: Misdreavus
description: It likes playing mischievous tricks$ such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.

name: Unown
description: Their shapes look like hieroglyphs on ancient tablets. It is said that the two are somehow related.

name: Wobbuffet
description: It hates light and shock. If attacked$ it inflates its body to build up its counterstrike.

name: Girafarig
description: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close$ it may react to your scent by biting.

name: Pineco
description: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

name: Forretress
description: Its entire body is shielded by a steel-hard shell. What lurks inside this shell is a total mystery.

name: Dunsparce
description: When spotted$ this Pokemon escapes backward by furiously boring into the ground with its tail.

name: Gligar
description: It flies straight at its target's face$ then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

name: Steelix
description: Its body has been compressed deep under the ground. As a result$ it is even harder than a diamond.

name: Snubbull
description: Although it looks frightening$ it is actually kind and affectionate. It is very popular among women.

name: Granbull
description: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked$ it flails about to fend off its attacker.

name: Qwilfish
description: To fire its poison spikes$ it must inflate its body by drinking over 2.6 gallons of water all at once.

name: Scizor
description: It swings its eye-patterned pincers up to scare its foes. This makes it look like it has three heads.

name: Shuckle
description: The berries it stores in its vase-like shell decompose and become a gooey liquid.

name: Heracross
description: This powerful Pokemon thrusts its prized horn under its enemies' bellies$ then lifts and throws them.

name: Sneasel
description: Its paws conceal sharp claws. If attacked$ it suddenly extends the claws and startles its enemy.

name: Teddiursa
description: If it finds honey$ its crescent mark glows. It always licks its paws because they're soaked with honey.

name: Ursaring
description: Although it is a good climber$ it prefers to snap trees with its forelegs and eat fallen berries.

name: Slugma
description: It never sleeps. It has to keep moving because if it stopped$ its magma body would cool and harden.

name: Magcargo
description: The shell on its back is just skin that has cooled and hardened. It breaks easily with a slight touch.

name: Swinub
description: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

name: Piloswine
description: Because the long hair all over its body obscures its sight$ it just keeps charging repeatedly.

name: Corsola
description: It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure because of its beauty.

name: Remoraid
description: It has superb accuracy. The water it shoots out can strike moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

name: Octillery
description: It traps foes with the suction cups on its tentacles$ then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

name: Delibird
description: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by its stored food.

name: Mantine
description: As it majestically swims$ it doesn't care if REMORAID attach to it for scavenging its leftovers.

name: Skarmory
description: Its sturdy wings look heavy$ but they are actually hollow and light$ allowing it to fly freely in the sky.

name: Houndour
description: It uses different kinds of cries for communicating with others of its kind and for pursuing its prey.

name: Houndoom
description: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth$ the pain will never go away.

name: Kingdra
description: It is said that it usually hides in underwater caves. It can create whirlpools by yawning.

name: Phanpy
description: It swings its long snout around playfully$ but because it is so strong$ that can be dangerous.

name: Donphan
description: It has sharp$ hard tusks and a rugged hide. Its tackle is strong enough to knock down a house.

name: Porygon2
description: This upgraded version of PORYGON is designed for space exploration. It can't fly$ however.

name: Stantler
description: The curved antlers subtly change the flow of air to create a strange space where reality is distorted.

name: Smeargle
description: A special fluid oozes from the tip of its tail. It paints the fluid everywhere to mark its territory.

name: Tyrogue
description: It is always bursting with energy. To make itself stronger$ it keeps on fighting even if it loses.

name: Hitmontop
description: If you are enchanted by its smooth$ dance-like kicks$ you may get a closer experience with one than you'd like.

name: Smoochum
description: Its lips are the most sensitive part of its body. It always uses its lips first to examine things.

name: Elekid
description: It rotates its arms to generate electricity$ but it tires easily$ so it only charges up a little bit.

name: Magby
description: Each and every time it inhales and exhales$ hot embers dribble from its mouth and nostrils.

name: Miltank
description: Its milk is packed with nutrition$ making it the ultimate beverage for the sick or weary.

name: Blissey
description: Anyone who takes even one taste of BLISSEY's egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.

name: Raikou
description: The rain clouds it carries let it fire thunderbolts at will. They say that it descended with lightning.

name: Entei
description: Volcanoes erupt when it barks. Unable to contain its sheer power$ it races headlong around the land.

name: Suicune
description: Said to be the embodiment of north winds$ it can instantly purify filthy$ murky water.

name: Larvitar
description: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain$ it falls asleep so it can grow.

name: Pupitar
description: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock$ and it is also very strong. Its thrashing can topple a mountain.

name: Tyranitar
description: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack$ so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

name: Lugia
description: It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.

name: Ho-Oh
description: Legends claim this Pokemon flies the world's skies continuously on its magnificent$ seven-colored wings.

name: Celebi
description: This Pokemon wanders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.

name: Treecko
description: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

name: Grovyle
description: It leaps from tree branch to tree branch quite swiftly. It shows astounding agility.

name: Sceptile
description: It agilely leaps about the jungle and uses the sharp leaves on its arms to strike its prey.

name: Torchic
description: Inside its body is a place where it keeps a small flame. Hug it! It will be as warm as a hot-water bottle.

name: Combusken
description: During a battle$ the hot flame in its body increases. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

name: Blaziken
description: It can clear a 30-story building in a leap. Its fiery punches scorch its foes.

name: Mudkip
description: Its power can crush boulders. It rests by covering itself with mud at the bottom of a river.

name: Marshtomp
description: Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has made its legs sturdy.

name: Swampert
description: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing$ it can break a boulder into pieces.

name: Poochyena
description: It chases its prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However$ it turns tail if the prey strikes back.

name: Mightyena
description: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

name: Zigzagoon
description: It gets interested in everything$ which is why it zigs and zags. It is good at finding items.

name: Linoone
description: When running in a straight line$ it can easily top 60 miles an hour. It has a tough time with curved roads.

name: Wurmple
description: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by  raising up the spikes on its rear.

name: Silcoon
description: Having wrapped silk around the branches of a tree$ it quiescently awaits evolution.

name: Beautifly
description: Vibrantly patterned wings are its prominent feature. It sucks sweet flower nectar with its long mouth.

name: Cascoon
description: It endures attacks with patience$ because the more pain before evolution$ the sturdier it becomes.

name: Dustox
description: It scatters its fine dust all over when it is attacked. It is a nocturnal Pokemon.

name: Lotad
description: Its leaf grew too large for it to live on land. That is how it began to live floating in the water.

name: Lombre
description: It is nocturnal and becomes active at nightfall. It feeds on aquatic mosses that grow in the riverbed.

name: Ludicolo
description: If it hears festive music$ it begins moving in rhythm in order to amplify its power.

name: Seedot
description: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

name: Nuzleaf
description: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head$ it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

name: Shiftry
description: It lives quietly in the deep forest. It is said to create chilly winter winds with the fans it holds.

name: Taillow
description: When it gets cold$ they migrate$ flying over 180 miles a day. It hunts for tasty prey.

name: Swellow
description: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

name: Wingull
description: It soars on updrafts without flapping its wings. It makes a nest on sheer cliffs at the sea's edge.

name: Pelipper
description: It protects its young in its beak. It bobs on waves$ resting on them on days when the waters are calm.

name: Ralts
description: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people's emotions.

name: Kirlia
description: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

name: Gardevoir
description: It unleashes psychokinetic energy at full power when protecting a Trainer it has bonded closely with.

name: Surskit
description: It secretes a thick$ sweet-scented syrup from the tip of its head. It lives on weed-choked ponds.

name: Masquerain
description: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction-- to and fro and sideways.

name: Shroomish
description: If it senses danger$ it scatters spores from the top of its head to protect itself.

name: Breloom
description: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

name: Slakoth
description: The way SLAKOTH lolls around makes anyone who watches it feel like doing the same.

name: Vigoroth
description: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

name: Slaking
description: The world's laziest Pokemon. It moves to another spot when there's no food left within its reach.

name: Nincada
description: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

name: Ninjask
description: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

name: Shedinja
description: A strange Pokemon--it flies without moving its wings$ has a hollow shell for a body$ and does not breathe.

name: Whismur
description: If it senses danger$ it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.

name: Loudred
description: It shouts loudly by inhaling air$ and then uses its well-developed stomach muscles to exhale.

name: Exploud
description: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor--or like an earthquake has struck.

name: Makuhita
description: It toughens up by slamming into thick trees over and over. It gains a sturdy body and dauntless spirit.

name: Hariyama
description: It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.

name: Azurill
description: Its tail is packed full of the nutrients it needs to grow.

name: Nosepass
description: If two of these meet$ they cannot get too close because their noses repel each other.

name: Skitty
description: It's adorable when it chases its own tail. It's difficult to earn its trust.

name: Delcatty
description: It dislikes dirty places. It often searches for a comfortable place in which to groom itself.

name: Sableye
description: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

name: Mawile
description: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

name: Aron
description: When it evolves$ it sheds the steel carapace that covered its whole body and develops a new one.

name: Lairon
description: It loves iron ore. Groups of them fight for territory by bashing one another with their steel bodies.

name: Aggron
description: You can tell its age by the length of its iron horns. It claims an entire mountain as its territory.

name: Meditite
description: It meditates to heighten its inner energy and to float in the air. It eats one berry a day.

name: Medicham
description: Through yoga training$ it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

name: Electrike
description: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

name: Manectric
description: Its nest can be found where a thunderbolt hits. It is discharging electricity from its mane.

name: Plusle
description: It absorbs electricity from telephone poles. It shorts out its body to create crackling noises.

name: Minun
description: Exposure to electricity from MINUN and PLUSLE promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.

name: Volbeat
description: It emits light from its tail to communicate. It loves the sweet aroma given off by ILLUMISE.

name: Illumise
description: Its fragrance attracts a swarm of VOLBEAT$ so they draw over 200 patterns in the night sky.

name: Roselia
description: ROSELIA that drink nutritionally rich springwater are said to reveal rare coloration when they bloom.

name: Gulpin
description: It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body$ with enzymes to dissolve anything.

name: Swalot
description: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

name: Carvanha
description: They form packs to attack boats and rip out their hulls to sink them. They live in rivers in the jungle.

name: Sharpedo
description: It can swim at speeds of 75 mph by jetting seawater through its body. It is the bandit of the sea.

name: Wailmer
description: It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows$ the higher it bounces.

name: Wailord
description: It is the largest of all identified Pokemon. They jump as a pack to herd their prey.

name: Numel
description: The flaming magma it stores in the hump on its back is the source of its tremendous power.

name: Camerupt
description: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.

name: Torkoal
description: You find abandoned coal mines full of them. They dig tirelessly in search of coal.

name: Spoink
description: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from CLAMPERL on its head.

name: Grumpig
description: It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

name: Spinda
description: The chances of two SPINDA having identical spot patterns is less than one in four billion.

name: Trapinch
description: Its nest is a sloped$ bowl-like pit in the desert. Once something has fallen in$ there is no escape.

name: Vibrava
description: It vibrates its wings vigorously$ creating ultrasonic waves that cause serious headaches.

name: Flygon
description: It is nicknamed “The Desert Spirit” because the flapping of its wings sounds like a woman singing.

name: Cacnea
description: It lives in arid locations. Its yellow flowers bloom once a year.

name: Cacturne
description: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

name: Swablu
description: Its wings bring cottony clouds to mind. It grooms with springwater and loves to sit on heads.

name: Altaria
description: It flies gracefully through the sky. Its melodic humming makes you feel like you're in a dream.

name: Zangoose
description: Its fur would all stand on end if it smelled a SEVIPER nearby. Its sharp claws tear up its foes.

name: Seviper
description: In battle$ it uses its bladed tail to counter any ZANGOOSE. It secretes a deadly venom in its tail.

name: Lunatone
description: It was discovered at the site of a meteor strike 40 years ago. Its stare can lull its foes to sleep.

name: Solrock
description: When it rotates itself$ it gives off light similar to the sun$ thus blinding its foes.

name: Barboach
description: BARBOACH uses its whiskers to taste things just as a person uses his or her tongue to taste things.

name: Whiscash
description: It claims a large swamp to itself. If a foe comes near it$ it sets off tremors by thrashing around.

name: Corphish
description: It was originally a Pokemon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.

name: Crawdaunt
description: A brutish Pokemon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

name: Baltoy
description: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some BALTOY have been seen spinning on their heads.

name: Claydol
description: It is said that it originates from clay dolls made by an ancient civilization.

name: Lileep
description: It disguises its tentacles as flowers to attract and catch prey. It became extinct in ancient times.

name: Cradily
description: It lives in warm seas. Its heavy body weighs it down so it won't get washed away in rough weather.

name: Anorith
description: An ancestral Pokemon that lived in the ocean. Over time$ its eight feet transformed into wings.

name: Armaldo
description: Its enormous$ retractable claws can cut through most anything. Its entire body is clad in sturdy plates.

name: Feebas
description: It is the shabbiest Pokemon of all. It forms in schools and lives at the bottom of rivers.

name: Milotic
description: It's said that a glimpse of a MILOTIC and its beauty will calm any hostile emotions you're feeling.

name: Castform
description: This Pokemon can change its cells$ taking different forms based on the temperature and humidity.

name: Kecleon
description: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.

name: Shuppet
description: It uses its horn to feed on envy and malice$ or so it's said. It's very active at night.

name: Banette
description: This Pokemon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

name: Duskull
description: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents$ it will spirit them away--or so it's said.

name: Dusclops
description: Anyone who dares peer into its body to see its spectral ball of fire will have their spirit stolen away.

name: Tropius
description: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It's a highly favored tropical snack.

name: Chimecho
description: It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.

name: Absol
description: It has the ability to foretell natural disasters. Its life span is over a hundred years.

name: Wynaut
description: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

name: Snorunt
description: It's said that if they are seen at midnight$ they'll cause heavy snow. They eat snow and ice to survive.

name: Glalie
description: It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere. It uses this power to freeze its foes.

name: Spheal
description: It crosses the oceans by rolling itself on drifting ice. Fluffy fur keeps it warm when the temperature is below freezing.

name: Sealeo
description: It has a very sensitive nose. It touches new things with its nose to examine them.

name: Walrein
description: It shatters drift ice with its strong tusks. Its thick layer of blubber repels enemy attacks.

name: Clamperl
description: When it evolves$ it makes a mysterious pearl that amplifies psychic powers when it's held.

name: Huntail
description: It lives deep in the pitch-dark sea. It attracts prey by moving its tail in mimicry of a small animal.

name: Gorebyss
description: Its pink body becomes more vivid with the rise of water temperatures in the springtime.

name: Relicanth
description: Discovered by chance during deep-sea explorations$ it has not changed since ancient times.

name: Luvdisc
description: Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places$ you would give a LUVDISC to someone you love.

name: Bagon
description: Its well-developed neck muscles and ironlike head can smash boulders into pieces.

name: Shelgon
description: It surrounds its body in an iron-hard shell to accumulate enough power to evolve.

name: Salamence
description: It's uncontrollable if enraged. It flies around spouting flames and scorching fields and mountains.

name: Beldum
description: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground's natural magnetism$ letting it float.

name: Metang
description: When two BELDUM fuse together$ a magnetic nervous system places their brains in union.

name: Metagross
description: It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.

name: Regirock
description: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.

name: Regice
description: It is said to have slept in a glacier for thousands of years. Its body can't be melted$ even by magma.

name: Registeel
description: Its body is said to be harder than any kind of metal. A study has revealed that its body is hollow.

name: Latias
description: It communicates using telepathy. Its body is covered in down that refracts light to make it invisible.

name: Latios
description: It understands human speech and is highly intelligent. It is a tender Pokemon that dislikes fighting.

name: Kyogre
description: A mythical Pokemon said to have swelled the seas with rain and tidal waves. It battled with GROUDON.

name: Groudon
description: Said to have expanded the lands by evaporating water with raging heat. It battled titanically with KYOGRE.

name: Rayquaza
description: It flies in the ozone layer$ way up high in the sky. Until recently$ no one had ever seen it.

name: Jirachi
description: Generations have believed that any wish written on a note on its head will come true when it awakens.

name: Deoxys
description: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokemon. It appears where auroras are seen.

name: Turtwig
description: Photosynthesis occurs across its body under the sun. The shell on its back is actually hardened soil.

name: Grotle
description: A GROTLE that lives in the forest is said to have its own secret springwater.

name: Torterra
description: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground$ a gigantic TORTERRA dwelled.

name: Chimchar
description: The gas made in its belly burns from its rear end. The fire burns weakly when it feels sick.

name: Monferno
description: A bigger fire on its tail and a brighter blue pattern on its face means its rank in its pack is higher.

name: Infernape
description: It tosses its enemies around with agility. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

name: Piplup
description: It doesn't like to be taken care of. It's difficult to bond with since it won't listen to its Trainer.

name: Prinplup
description: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

name: Empoleon
description: It avoids unnecessary disputes$ but it will decimate anything that threatens its pride.

name: Starly
description: They flock around mountains and fields$ chasing after bug Pokemon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

name: Staravia
description: They maintain huge flocks$ although fierce scuffles break out between various flocks.

name: Staraptor
description: When STARAVIA evolve into STARAPTOR$ they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

name: Bidoof
description: It lives in groups by the water.  It chews up boulders and trees around its nest with its incisors.

name: Bibarel
description: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.

name: Kricketot
description: When its antennae hit each other$ it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

name: Kricketune
description: By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly$ it produces a captivating sound.

name: Shinx
description: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. Its fur glows when it's in trouble.

name: Luxio
description: By gathering their tails together$ they collectively generate powerful electricity from their claws.

name: Luxray
description: LUXRAY's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

name: Budew
description: When it feels the sun's warm touch$ it opens its bud to release pollen. It lives alongside clear pools.

name: Roserade
description: Its sweet aroma attracts prey. Then it spews poison. The more toxic it is$ the sweeter its aroma.

name: Cranidos
description: CRANIDOS toughen up their already rock-hard heads by headbutting one another.

name: Rampardos
description: Its skull withstands impacts of any magnitude. As a result$ its brain never gets the chance to grow.

name: Shieldon
description: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

name: Bastiodon
description: When attacked$ they form a wall. Their rock-hard faces serve to protect them from the attacks.

name: Burmy
description: It covers itself with a cloak to shelter from the cold. When it's hot$ its cloak is thinner.

name: Wormadam
description: It is said that a WORMADAM that evolves on a cold day will have a thicker cloak.

name: Mothim
description: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the COMBEE hive.

name: Combee
description: At night$ COMBEE sleep in a group of about a thousand$ packed closely together in a lump.

name: Vespiquen
description: It raises grubs in the holes in its body. It secretes pheromones to control COMBEE.

name: Pachirisu
description: It's one of the kinds of Pokemon  with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

name: Buizel
description: It inflates its flotation sac$ keeping its face above water in order to watch for prey movement.

name: Floatzel
description: With its flotation sac inflated$ it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Cherubi
description: It evolves by sucking the energy out of the small ball where it had been storing nutrients.

name: Cherrim
description: During times of strong sunlight$ its bud blooms$ its petals open fully$ and it becomes very active.

name: Shellos
description: Its shape and coloration vary$ depending on its habitat.

name: Gastrodon
description: When its natural enemy attacks$ it oozes purple fluid and escapes.

name: Ambipom
description: They live on large trees. They are said to communicate by connecting their tails to those of others.

name: Drifloon
description: It is whispered that any child who mistakes DRIFLOON for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.

name: Drifblim
description: It can generate and release gas within its body. That's how it can control the altitude of its drift.

name: Buneary
description: You can tell how it feels by the way it rolls its ears. When it's scared$ both ears are rolled up.

name: Lopunny
description: It sheds its fur twice a year. Its winter fur is soft and fluffy.

name: Mismagius
description: Its cries sound like incantations to torment the foe. It appears where you least expect it.

name: Honchkrow
description: It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its MURKROW followers.

name: Glameow
description: When it's happy$ GLAMEOW demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail$ like a dancing ribbon.

name: Purugly
description: It would claim another Pokemon's nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

name: Chingling
description: It emits high-frequency cries that  people can't hear. Once it starts$ it can cry for an awfully long time.

name: Stunky
description: The foul fluid from its rear is so revolting that it can make people feel queasy up to a mile and a quarter away.

name: Skuntank
description: It attacks by spraying a repugnant fluid from its tail$ but the stench dulls after a few squirts.

name: Bronzor
description: Ancient people believed that the pattern on BRONZOR's back contained a mysterious power.

name: Bronzong
description: Ancient people believed that petitioning BRONZONG for rain was the way to make crops grow.

name: Bonsly
description: In order to adjust the level of fluids in its body$ it exudes water from its eyes. This makes it appear to be crying.

name: Mime Jr.
description: In an attempt to confuse its enemy$ it mimics the enemy's movements. Then it wastes no time in making itself scarce!

name: Happiny
description: It carefully carries a round$ white rock that it thinks is an egg. It's bothered by how curly its hair looks.

name: Chatot
description: It mimics the cries of other Pokemon to trick them into thinking it's one of them. This way they won't attack it.

name: Spiritomb
description: It was formed by uniting 108 spirits. It has been bound to the Odd Keystone to keep it from doing any mischief.

name: Gible
description: It nests in horizontal holes warmed by geothermal heat. Foes who get too close can expect to be pounced on and bitten.

name: Gabite
description: As it digs to expand its nest$ it habitually digs up gems that it then hoards in its nest.

name: Garchomp
description: Its body is covered in fine scales that reduce drag$ enabling it to fly at high speeds.

name: Munchlax
description: It conceals food under the long fur on its body. It carts around this food stash and swallows it without chewing.

name: Riolu
description: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

name: Lucario
description: It's said that no foe can remain invisible to LUCARIO$ since it can detect auras. Even foes it could not otherwise see.

name: Hippopotas
description: It shrouds itself in sand to ward off germs. It travels easily through the sands of the desert.

name: Hippowdon
description: It brandishes its gaping mouth in a display of fearsome strength. It raises vast quantities of sand while attacking.

name: Skorupi
description: It burrows under the sand to lie in wait for prey. Its tail claws can inject its prey with a savage poison.

name: Drapion
description: It attacks people and Pokemon that cross the desert. This has only furthered its bad reputation.

name: Croagunk
description: Fluid squeezed from its finger$ albeit poisonous$ is a significant ingredient in remedies for lower-back pain.

name: Toxicroak
description: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes$ it weaves its flexible body in close$ then lunges out with its poisonous claws.

name: Carnivine
description: It walks around on its tentacles in search of a tree branch where it can dangle down and ambush prey.

name: Finneon
description: Swimming and fluttering its two tail fins$ it looks like a BEAUTIFLY. At night$ the patterns on its tail fins softly shine.

name: Lumineon
description: LUMINEON swimming in the darkness of the deep sea look like stars shining in the night sky.

name: Mantyke
description: When it swims close to the surface of the ocean$ people aboard ships are able to observe the pattern on its back.

name: Snover
description: During cold seasons$ it migrates to the mountain's lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

name: Abomasnow
description: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

name: Weavile
description: It lives in snowy regions. It carves patterns in trees with its claws as a signal to others.

name: Magnezone
description: Exposure to a special magnetic field changed MAGNETON's molecular structure$ turning it into MAGNEZONE.

name: Lickilicky
description: Its saliva can decompose anything. It wraps its long tongue around things to coat them with its sticky saliva.

name: Rhyperior
description: From holes in its palms$ it fires out GEODUDE. Its carapace  can withstand volcanic eruptions.

name: Tangrowth
description: When it remains still$ it appears to be a large shrub. Unsuspecting prey that wander near get ensnared by its vines.

name: Electivire
description: As its electric charge amplifies$ blue sparks begin to crackle between its horns.

name: Magmortar
description: It blasts fireballs of over 3$600 degrees Fahrenheit out of its arms. Its breath also sears and sizzles.

name: Togekiss
description: As everyone knows$ it visits peaceful regions$ bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.

name: Yanmega
description: This six-legged Pokemon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

name: Leafeon
description: When you see LEAFEON asleep in a patch of sunshine$ you'll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.

name: Glaceon
description: It causes small ice crystals to form by lowering the temperature of the surrounding atmosphere.

name: Gliscor
description: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

name: Mamoswine
description: A frozen MAMOSWINE was dug from ice dating back 10$000 years. This Pokemon has been around a long$ long$ long time.

name: Porygon-Z
description: Its programming was modified to enable it to travel through alien dimensions. Seems there might have been an error...

name: Gallade
description: Because it can sense what its foe is thinking$ its attacks burst out first$ fast$ and fierce.

name: Probopass
description: It controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force. With them$ it can attack the foe from three directions.

name: Dusknoir
description: This feared Pokemon is said to travel to worlds unknown. Some even believe that it takes lost spirits along with it.

name: Froslass
description: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly�-60 degrees Fahrenheit. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

name: Rotom
description: Research continues on this Pokemon$ which could be the power source of a unique motor.

name: Uxie
description: According to some sources$ this Pokemon provided people with the intelligence necessary to solve various problems.

name: Mesprit
description: This Pokemon is said to have endowed the human heart with emotions$ such as sorrow and joy.

name: Azelf
description: This Pokemon is said to have endowed humans with the determination needed to face any of life's difficulties.

name: Dialga
description: This Pokemon completely controls the flow of time. It uses its power to travel at will through the past and future.

name: Palkia
description: Its total control over the boundaries of space enable it to transport itself to faraway places or even other dimensions.

name: Heatran
description: Boiling blood$ like magma$ circulates through its body. It makes its dwelling place in volcanic caves.

name: Regigigas
description: It is believed to have shaped REGIROCK$ REGICE$ and REGISTEEL out of clay$ ice$ and magma.

name: Giratina
description: This Pokemon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours$ where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

name: Cresselia
description: Those who sleep holding CRESSELIA's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Phione
description: When the water warms$ they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

name: Manaphy
description: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokemon.

name: Darkrai
description: It chases people and Pokemon from its territory by causing them to experience deep$ nightmarish slumbers.

name: Shaymin
description: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings  of gratitude are the message it delivers.

name: Arceus
description: According to the legends of Sinnoh$ this Pokemon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.

name: Zorua
description: To protect themselves from danger$ they hide their true identities by transforming into people and Pok�mon.

name: Zoroark
